        <marginalia hand="Italian" method="pen">
            <language ident="FR">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="head">
                    <marginalia_text>Le Duc Richard de Normandie, regarda, que par souffrir ne obeijr il nauroit point de paix, si ordonna ses gens par telle maniere, que ceulx du pais D'Auge, 
                        et de [Hommois?] deffendroient la terre contre Rotrou, le Conte du Perche, et de Belesme qui faisoient guerre par deuers Sees et le pais de la etainsi y adiousta les Aurenchinoys contre ceulx de Flandres, 
                        et D Amiennoys [?st] les Cauchoys, ceulx des Contez D'Eu, et d'Aumalle. Et il rotint auec Luy les brettons, et ceulx de Constentin.</marginalia_text>  <!-- DO: Unsure of some words here -->
                    <person name="Richard I of Normandy"/>
                    <person name="Rotrou I, Count of Perche"/>
                    <location name="Pays d'Auge"/>
                    <!--JG: Location needs to be added-->
                    <location name="Belleme"/>
                    <location name="Sees"/>
                    <location name="Avranches"/>
                    <location name="Flanders"/>
                    <location name="Amiens"/>
                    <location name="Pays de Caux"/>
                    <location name="Eu"/>
                    <location name="Aumale"/>
                    <location name="Brittany"/>
                    <location name="Coutances"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The Duke Richard of Normandy, having seen that through enduring [resistance to obedience] he [nauroit?] a period of peace, if having ordered the people in such a way, 
                that those of Pays d'Auge, and those of [Hommois], would defend the land against Rotrou, the Count of Perche, and of Belleme, who waged a war against Sees and 
                the country there and thus having added the people of Avranches against those of Flanders, and those of Amiens, [?] the people of Pays de Caux, those of the communes of Eu and Aumale. 
                And he [?] with him the Bretons, and the people of Coutances.</translation>  <!-- DO: Translation needs revising; also I can't actually identify 'Hommois' as a place so might be something else  -->
        </marginalia>
        
